== Rice ==

Boil a full #kettle{}. While you wait, halve, peel and thinly slice the
@Echalion shallot{1}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Jasmine rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{}
and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Chicken ==

While the rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on
medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and shallot to the pan
and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Fry until the chicken is golden brown on the outside and cooked through,
~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Stir-Fry ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @sugar snap peas{80%g} widthways. Drain the @king prawns{150%g}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

== Assemble ==

When the chicken is cooked, add the prawns, garlic and sugar snaps to the
frying pan.

Stir-fry until the sugar snaps are just tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir the @teriyaki sauce{150%g}, @sambal paste{15%g}(add less if you'd prefer
milder), @water{50%ml} and half the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g} into the
pan.

Simmer until the sauce is slightly thickened and the prawns are cooked through,
~{3-4%minutes}, then remove from the heat. Taste and season if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the
> middle.

Add a splash more water if you feel it needs it.

== To Serve ==

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the sambal teriyaki chicken and prawn stir-fry.

Finish by scattering over the remaining sesame seeds. Enjoy!